Run this and it will add an icon into your System Tray which gives you a character count of your clipboard.

It has a global keyboard shortcut of Win+C.  If you don't like that then bug me until I change it (or send me a pull request*.)

Questions, etc. to andrew@ducker.org.uk - I may mention updates at http://andrewducker.livejournal.com or I may not.

Downloadable from http://dl.dropbox.com/u/400524/ClipboardTextCounter.exe



*I've never had a pull request.  They sound like fun.  In a dirty kind of way.